  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">East Africa Crisis 2016/17</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought, food insecurity and conflict have led to a sharp increase in needs across east Africa in 2017, and in particular in South Sudan, Somalia, Kenya and Ethiopia. Neighbouring countries have also been affected, especially those receiving high numbers of refugees, such as Uganda. This crisis has led to a significant international humanitarian response in each affected country, including from the RC Movement. BRC has also been responding, through the launch of its own public appeal, engagement with the DEC East Africa appeal, and through the allocation of funding and resources to various operations throughout the region.</narrative>
  </description>
